# Implementation Plan - Flutter Geo Tag Camera App

We will create a premium Flutter application in the workspace directory. It will feature a real-time camera view, live GPS/geotag card overlay, image filters, and composite image saving/exporting.

## Key Packages to Include
- `camera`: For camera capture and preview.
- `geolocator`: For obtaining GPS coordinates (lat, long).
- `geocoding`: For reverse-geocoding coordinates to a human-readable address.
- `path_provider` & `path`: For managing local image storage.
- `image`: For image filters, overlays, and drawing the geotag card onto the captured photo file.

## Application Architecture & UI
- **Camera Screen**: Displays the live camera view, overlayed with a custom glassmorphic Card showcasing the address, coordinates, and weather variables. Includes controls to toggle templates, adjust filters/effects, switch cameras, and the shutter capture button.
- **Image Filters**: Real-time camera visual effects using Flutter's `ColorFiltered` widget. When captured, we will apply the chosen color matrix or filter using the Dart `image` package to bake the filter into the saved JPEG.
- **Composite Image Renderer**: Renders the captured photo, processes it with the active filter, and draws the geotag card watermark (text, coordinates, and mini map mockup) using the Dart `Canvas` or `image` package libraries.
- **Gallery Screen**: A grid view of captured geotagged photos with capabilities to view, download, or delete them.

## Proposed Changes

### [Flutter Setup]
We will run `flutter create --org com.geocamera .` to initialize a new Flutter project in the current folder.

### [Pubspec Dependencies]
Modify `pubspec.yaml` to include:
- `camera`
- `geolocator`
- `geocoding`
- `path_provider`
- `image`
- `intl` (for dates)

### [Core Dart Implementation]
- `lib/main.dart`: Initializer, theme config, and main route.
- `lib/screens/camera_screen.dart`: Custom Camera controller, real-time location integration, filters list, and overlay templates.
- `lib/screens/gallery_screen.dart`: Shows saved photos stored locally in the app documents directory.
- `lib/widgets/geotag_overlay.dart`: UI widget representing the glassmorphic card.
- `lib/services/image_processor.dart`: Generates the final geotagged JPEG by merging the camera image with coordinates, addresses, and weather variables.

